  "cooking_instructions": [
    {
      "instruction": "<p><strong>Preheat</strong> the oven to 220&deg;C/ 200&deg;C (fan)/ 425&deg;F/ Gas 7</p>\r\n<p><strong>Cut</strong> the broccoli florets and the stem<span class=\"text-danger\">[s]</span>&nbsp;into bite-size pieces</p>\r\n<p><strong>Add</strong> them to&nbsp;a baking tray, drizzle with 1-2 tbsp vegetable oil and season with salt and pepper, then put them in the oven&nbsp;for 10 min or until starting to brown</p>",
      "order": 1,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/246.-step1.-x200.jpg",
            "width": 200
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/246.-step1.-x400.jpg",
            "width": 400
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/246.-step1.-x700.jpg",
            "width": 700
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/246.-step1.-x1000.jpg",
            "width": 1000
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/246.-step1.-x1500.jpg",
            "width": 1500
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p><strong>Meanwhile</strong>, boil a kettle&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p><strong>Bash</strong> the lemongrass&nbsp;with a rolling pin, cut it <span class=\"text-danger\">[them]</span>&nbsp;down the middle lengthways, remove the tough outer layers (keep them for later!) and chop the softer inner stem<span class=\"text-danger\">[s]</span>&nbsp;finely</p>\r\n<p><strong>Peel</strong> and chop the garlic and the ginger coarsely</p>",
      "order": 2,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/246.-step2.-x200.jpg",
            "width": 200
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/246.-step2.-x400.jpg",
            "width": 400
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/246.-step2.-x700.jpg",
            "width": 700
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/246.-step2.-x1000.jpg",
            "width": 1000
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/246.-step2.-x1500.jpg",
            "width": 1500
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p><strong>Add</strong>&nbsp;the rice, 350ml <span class=\"text-danger\">[700ml]</span>&nbsp;water and the outer lemongrass layers to a pot (with a lid) and bring it to the boil over a high heat</p>\r\n<p><strong>Once</strong> boiling, reduce the heat to very low and cook, covered, for 10-15 min or until all the water has absorbed and the rice is cooked</p>",
      "order": 3,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/246.-step3.-x200.jpg",
            "width": 200
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/246.-step3.-x400.jpg",
            "width": 400
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/246.-step3.-x700.jpg",
            "width": 700
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/246.-step3.-x1000.jpg",
            "width": 1000
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/246.-step3.-x1500.jpg",
            "width": 1500
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p><strong>Meanwhile</strong>, blitz the ginger, garlic, lemongrass stems and chilli (can't handle the heat? Go easy!) in a blender to form a rough paste (alternatively, chop very finely)</p>\r\n<p><strong>Combine</strong> the paste, pork mince, breadcrumbs, 1 <span class=\"text-danger\">[2]</span>&nbsp;sachet<span class=\"text-danger\">[s]</span>&nbsp;soy sauce in a mixing bowl with a pinch of salt and pepper</p>\r\n<p><strong>Shape</strong> 6 <span class=\"text-danger\">[12]</span>&nbsp;meatballs from the mixture</p>",
      "order": 4,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/246.-step4.-x200.jpg",
            "width": 200
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/246.-step4.-x400.jpg",
            "width": 400
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/246.-step4.-x700.jpg",
            "width": 700
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/246.-step4.-x1000.jpg",
            "width": 1000
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/246.-step4.-x1500.jpg",
            "width": 1500
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p><strong>Spread</strong> the sesame seeds out on a plate, roll the meatballs into the seeds to coat them evenly</p>\r\n<p><strong>Heat</strong> 1-2 tbsp vegetable oil in a large pan (preferably non-stick)&nbsp;over a high heat</p>\r\n<p><strong>Once</strong>&nbsp;hot, add the meatballs and cook for 3-4 min or until the meatballs have browned on all sides</p>",
      "order": 5,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/246.-step5.-x200.jpg",
            "width": 200
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/246.-step5.-x400.jpg",
